id: pm-q9yt
title: "Decision: Cap telemetry result_summary payload size"
description: "Decision needed: how to prevent telemetry events from exceeding proxy/CDN body size limits. Options: (1) Cap total serialized size of result_summary to 100KB, (2) Truncate sample values to max 1KB each, (3) Add pre-enqueue size guard that drops result_summary if event exceeds 500KB, (4) Reduce array sample limit from 5 to 2 and object key limit from 25 to 10."
type: Decision
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: audit,decision,pm-cli,telemetry
created_at: "2026-05-01T18:05:36.013Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-01T18:20:53.394Z"
author: audit-agent
acceptance_criteria: Decision documented with rationale and implementation plan
parent: pm-2eb3
dependencies[2]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-2eb3,parent,"2026-05-01T18:05:36.013Z",audit-agent,null
  pm-ntr0,blocks,"2026-05-01T18:05:36.013Z",audit-agent,null
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T18:05:36.013Z",audit-agent,Prefer option 3 (pre-enqueue size guard) because it handles all edge cases without changing the capture fidelity for small/medium commands.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T18:05:36.013Z",audit-agent,"Telemetry payloads should always be bounded by total serialized size,not just array/object element counts."
close_reason: "Decided: option 3 (pre-enqueue size guard at 512KB) combined with depth-limited sanitization (max depth 6) and max-attempts pruning (15). Implemented and verified with all 1087 tests passing."
body: "Context: Cloudflare returns error 1010 (body too large) for events over ~1MB. Current summarizeResult() limits arrays to 5 samples and objects to 25 keys, but nested values are unbounded. The 130MB queue with 70-retry entries needs both a fix and a cleanup. Recommendation: Option 3 (pre-enqueue size guard) is simplest and most robust - serialize the event, check byte length, and truncate result_summary progressively if over threshold. Also add a gc sub-command or health remediation to prune stuck queue entries."
